{
  "texts": [
    "The structure and training strategies of GAN-LSTM are shown in Fig. 7.",
    "The training objective of the discriminator D is to distinguish between predictions generated by the generator G and the ground truth, by minimizing the loss function L d.",
    "The binary cross-entropy loss is utilized as the similarity evaluation metric, with the objective of training D to output 1 when presented with ground truth as input and 0 when presented with predictions as input:",
    "Here, L bce is the binary cross-entropy loss, which is defined as follows:",
    "where p denotes the label (0 or 1) and p denotes the logit value between 0 and 1."
  ]
}